name.en: Local Organic Mushrooms, Crimini - BC Grown
description.en: Not only are numerous health advantages offered by these little wonders (including anti-cancer benefits, antioxidant benefits, and immune system support), but organic crimini mushrooms taste great too. Crimini mushrooms are juvenile portabellas (aka portobellos) which have a deeper, denser, earthier flavour than White mushrooms and are the perfect addition to a delicious meal.

description.en: The Medjool Date, once a delicacy know only to royalty, is now the most popular date in the world. Per Serving Size: 2 to 3 dates (40g) dates have: Calories: 140 - Sodium: 10mg - Total Carbohydrates: 36g - Dietary Fiber - 3g - Sugars - 29g - Protein: 1g - Potassium: 200mg - Calcium: 2% & Iron: 2% of Daily Recommended Value

If it’s not perfect, we’ll refund you, no questions asked. Try our organic Gala apples sautéed in our Kale with Sautéed Apple and Onion recipe. Check out our recipe page for more meal ideas with fresh Gala apples. Organic Gala apples can be delivered to most areas on Vancouver Island. Have a look at our delivery page for times and routes across the island.

description.en: There are over 30 species of mint, the two most popular and widely available being peppermint and spearmint. Peppermint has bright green leaves, purple-tinged stems and a peppery flavor. Spearmint leaves are gray-green or true green and have a milder flavor and fragrance. Mint can be used as a tea, added to boiled potatoes, your fruit or veggy salad, fresh juices, or favourite recipes.

Cut a kiwi in half or mash the flesh, rub it over meat, and leave to stand for at least 15-30 minutes.

name.en: Local Organic Mushrooms, Shiitake - BC Grown
description.en: Shiitake is the second most widely cultivated mushroom in the world and highly prized for its flavor and health-promoting properties. 'Shii' is Japanese for oak and 'take' means mushroom. Shiitakes provide high levels of protein (18% by mass), potassium, niacin and B vitamins, calcium, magnesium and phosphorus. The mushroom has all essential amino acids. Shiitakes have natural antiviral and immunity-boosting properties and are used nutritionally to fight viruses, lower cholesterol and regulate blood pressure.

description.en: Butternut squash is a mildly sweet, nutty squash, and is easier to prepare than other squashes because of its thin skin. The smooth creamy texture of our organic butternut squash is an ideal choice in tons of recipes, and it sometimes replaces pumpkin in pumpkin pie recipes. Try it roasted and lightly topped with cracked pepper, sea salt, and a hint of brown sugar.

description.en: Love the comfort of pasta but hate the added carbs? Try our organic spaghetti squash. When cooked, it has thin long yellow strands that can be substituted for pasta in any of your favourite recipes, and the subtle taste and mild crunch gives your meal a low-carb, healthy touch. Try it nice and simple: topped with cracked black pepper and all-natural sea salt. Have your organic spaghetti squash delivered straight to your door along with your other fresh produce to maximize SPUD.ca’s grocery delivery services.

description.en: A member of the rose family, these berries are grown all over the world for their sweet, fragrant flavour. Not only are these strawberries succulent, scrumptious and satisfying, they are also organic; therefore, no chemicals or synthetic pesticides were used in the farming methods. Here at SPUD, our produce team ensures that our plump organic strawberries arrive at your doorstep as though they were just picked from the farm. Strawberries are extremely versatile and can be added to tons of dishes for optimum flavour. Try making our Rhubarb and Strawberry Compote with Mint to serve over vanilla ice cream for a yummy dessert!
